etymology.description: Semantic 丷 (divide) + Phonetic 豕 (suì, "pig") = phonetic component without direct semantic meaning
etymology.interpretation: The character 㒸 acts primarily as a phonetic component in other compounds, like 遂(遂) (suì, "comply"). Its components do not directly convey a clear semantic meaning, and the 豕 (豕) (shǐ, "pig") serves mainly a phonetic purpose in this context.
